<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--AssaultRifle     02-22 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Assault Rifle,0171</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Kills Brother With AK-47 Replica</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNHALL, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 41-year-old man who said he was tired of
being bullied shot his older brother to death with a replica of an
AK-47 assault rifle, police said.
   Paul M. Kacsmar was charged with criminal homicide in the death
of Francis Kacsmar, 46, and held in the Allegheny County Jail
without bond.
   Police said Paul Kacsmar called them Tuesday evening. When they
arrived, Kacsmar blurted out he had shot his brother because he was
tired of being bullied. The two men had shared a home in this
blue-collar community on Pittsburgh's southeastern border.
   Francis, shot four times in the chest, was found dead in the
living room when police arrived. A Valmet 62-S rifle, a replica of
the Soviet AK-47 military assault rifle, was discovered in the
kitchen, police said.
   Police found about 50 other guns in the house in addition to a
collection of military and weapons magazines and a collection of
miniature soldiers.
</TEXT>
