<FIRST>u a AM-GunBan     02-22 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Gun Ban,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Suburban Chicago Village Bans Handguns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMETTE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Village trustees passed an ordinance
Tuesday that bans the sale and possession of handguns.
   Wilmette, north of Chicago, is bounded by Winnetka, where Laurie
Dann entered a school last May and fatally shot one child and
injured five other youngsters. Later she injured a man and killed
herself.
   Since that incident, gun-control activists, including Philip
Andrew, a college student who survived the ordeal, have been
advocating a ban in many of the affluent Lake Michigan communities.
   ``We're really pleased,'' said Christine Crosh, a member of a
group called the Wilmette Coalition to Ban Handguns. ``There's been
tremendous community support for this.''
   The vote was 7-0.
