<HEAD>Police Dismantle Rocket Aimed At Military Junta Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police dismantled an anti-tank rocket
guerrillas set up on a downtown hill and timed to automatically fire
at the high-rise building that houses the ruling military junta,
authorities said.
   The rocket was found by a cleaning worker and dismantled shortly
before it was to fire at noon Tuesday, a police communique said.
   Next to the rocket a leaflet was found reading ``Manuel Rodriguez
Front, National Patriotic War. Free Motherland or Death.''
   The Manuel Rodriguez Front is the main leftist urban guerrilla
band fighting the government of military President Augusto Pinochet.
   The rocket was aimed at the Diego Portales Building, which houses
the four-man military junta that Pinochet leads.
   It was not immediately known whether any of the four were in the
building when the rocket was found.
