<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--DigitSwitch     02-22 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Digit Switch,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Doctors Replace Man's Severed Thumb With Big Toe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANN ARBOR, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Doctors used a man's big toe to replace
his right thumb after the finger was severed during an industrial
accident, hospital officials said.
   David Hemmert, 19, of Owosso underwent the 14-hour operation Jan.
24, said officials at St. Joseph Mercy Hospital here.
   ``To tell you the truth, when I was told about this kind of
surgery, I wasn't too hip on it at first,'' Hemmert said Tuesday.
``After thinking it all over, I decided to go for it _ and I gained
more than I lost.''
   Hemmert was working for a window frame company when he
accidentally cut off his right thumb with an industrial saw, said
his surgeon, Dr. David Hing. The severed digit was replaced with the
big toe on the man's right foot.
   Hing said the man's new ``thumb'' will allow him to again grasp
objects with his injured hand.
