<FIRST>r a PM-Lites     02-22 0393</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lites,0406</SECOND>
<HEAD>On the Light Side</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BECKLEY, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The world's biggest block of cheese was
beginning to show its age, but that didn't put off residents of this
small town _ not necessarily cheese-lovers _ who came out to see the
wonder.
   ``It's the biggest thing I've ever seen in the way of cheese,''
John Watson said of the 40,060-pound block of cheddar. ``It looks a
little moldy on the top but that doesn't hurt cheese.''
   The immense milk curd, listed as the world's largest cheese by
the Guinness Book of World Records, has been touring the country
since May as a promotion for an Oklahoma City food company. It
stopped at a supermarket in Beckley, about 50 miles southeast of
Charleston, on Monday.
   ``It doesn't look like it weighs 40,000 pounds,'' said Florence
Church. ``But wouldn't it make a lot of lovely cheeseburgers?''
   Even 6-year-old Ashley Skeens was impressed.
   ``I hate cheese. I just wanted to look at it,'' Ashley said.
   Pat Patterson, the truck driver who is carting the cheese named
Belle of Wisconsin, said it will be sliced and sold in commemorative
packages when the tour ends.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WELLINGTON, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Radio announcer Dennis Heart broadcast a
wedding proposal to his girlfriend Joann on his morning show, then
found he had to sort out the responses.
   Several women named Joann phoned in to accept his offer. What's
more, ``We had two women call who said they'd be willing to change
their name to Joann,'' said Anita Lynn, the show's newscaster on
station WKGR.
   Joann Mileni, who lives with Heart in this town just west of Palm
Beach, was driving near Boca Raton when she heard the proposal
Monday morning. But rather than call in with her answer, she headed
straight for the station's Fort Pierce studio about 60 miles up the
coast.
   ``I've been doing some soul searching,'' Heart said, as the theme
song from Romeo and Juliet played in the background. ``I've just
been going through the James Brown and Aretha Franklin records last
night. As ... you know, I've been involved with my lady Joann for
almost a year, and I thought I'd take this time to ask her to marry
me.''
   Nearly an hour later, Ms. Mileni walked in the studio and
accepted, but only after Heart repeated the proposal on his knees.
</TEXT>
