<TEXT>
   A policeman has been fired for standing aside and
watching while three television reporters were beaten up, the
official Xinhua News Agency said Wednesday.
   The report said the reporters from a TV station in Jiangxi
province, southern China, were on their way to cover a story in
November and asked the policeman to help them through a traffic jam.
   Instead, the policeman pulled them out of their car and watched
