northwestern Shaanxi province dismissed a lawsuit filed by a police
officer who said local journalists had defamed him with reports his
police station was crude and unsympathetic toward farmers. The judge
ruled the court must support constructive journalistic criticism of
public institutions and protect journalists' rights.
