<HEAD>Clerk In Bulletproof Cage Sneers at Robbery Attempt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A store clerk in a bulletproof glass
cashier's cage told police she simply grinned and telephoned for
help when a man who said he had a gun tried to rob her.
   Night shift clerk Judy Frisco, 39, said the hold-up man came into
her service station-grocery early Tuesday and said, ``I want your
money. ... I have a 9mm and I am going to get you. ... I can blow
this window away.''
   But Ms. Frisco apparently did not believe he could. She began
dialing.
   Police reported that the would-be robber ``apparently became
weary from the neglect shown ... and ran.''
