<HEAD>Three Bodies Recovered From Grain Mill Fire; Four Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three bodies have been recovered
from a grain mill that was destroyed in an explosion and subsequent
fire, but four workers remained missing, it was reported Wednesday.
   Seven people were hospitalized, the official CTK news agency
said, adding only that six of them were ``out of danger.''
   The explosion took place just after noon Tuesday in a four-story
grain mill at Surany in western Slovakia.
   The Communist Party daily newspaper Rude Pravo said 15 fire
brigades from surrounding towns were called in to help extinguish
